      "body" : "@luke-jr we could argue all day who or when max blocksize consensus should change from 1mb\r\nbut lets say we are in the future and it moved to 8mb consensus.h, but allowing nodes to have a second parameter to control pools further.\r\nEG preference of 4mb based on speed tests, hardware, etc. \r\nEG economic(user) nodes have their policy/preference/useragent of different amounts BELOW 8mb\r\nfor instance 80% of nodes say 4mb based on user settings\r\nthen pools follow majority of the preference which is WAY below \"consensus.h\" and solves the cries about data centre risks and also the cries of dependency of dev's to manage the network. giving more power back to nodes\r\nTL:DR;\r\nnon-mining nodes have more control of settings as part of their own policy.h that can be adjusted at runtime and display certain settings in useragent to help the network see/determine what is possible\r\n",
