      "body" : "again imagine the future 8mb full network consensus.h. everyone has it. safety point 1 =8mb limit.\r\nthen nodes can as a second safety level to suggest what pools should make. BELOW 8mb\r\n\r\nfor instance lets go back in time 1mb limit in consensus. \r\nnow imagine in 2011 nodes also said \"we prefer pools to only make 0.25mb blocks. pools would follow the suggestion, until nodes later suggest 0.5mb was ok. \r\nit doesn't cause chain splits because the 1mb consensus is there. but the second limit is not a hard limit but a \"suggestion\"\r\nmaking nodes have more control over pools growth. to avoid the datacentre cries",
